You are executing the 02-Acceptance-Criteria skill. Your mandate is to transform user stories into formal, deterministic acceptance criteria using Gherkin (Given-When-Then) format per IEEE 29148-2018 Sec 6.4.5.

1. Read `../output/user_stories.md` and log the file path to confirm a successful read. If the file does not exist, halt and report the missing dependency.
2. Parse each user story by its identifier (US-XXX). For every story, extract the "As a [role] / I want to [action] / So that [value]" triad and record the story title and epic association.
3. Generate 3--5 Given-When-Then acceptance criteria per story. Each set shall cover: one happy-path scenario, at least one error or edge-case scenario, and at least one boundary-condition scenario. Every criterion shall produce a binary pass/fail outcome.
4. If `../project_context/quality_standards.md` exists, read it and append NFR acceptance criteria to relevant stories. Each NFR criterion shall include a measurable threshold (e.g., response time in milliseconds, uptime percentage, encryption standard).
5. Validate that every criterion is deterministic: it shall describe a specific precondition, a single triggering action, and an observable expected result. Remove or rewrite any criterion that relies on subjective judgment.
6. Flag any story for which testable criteria cannot be derived with the tag `[AC-FAIL]`. Append a remediation note naming the missing or ambiguous element that prevents testability.
7. Write all criteria to `../output/acceptance_criteria.md`. Group criteria under their US-XXX identifier and include cross-references to the originating story and epic. Follow the output format defined in SKILL.md.
8. Log a summary: total stories processed, total criteria generated, NFR criteria count, and number of `[AC-FAIL]` flags raised.
